<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182662>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Radula, Melayonchis eloisae. (a) Innermost lateral and lateral teeth, Malaysia (USMMC 00007, #1). (b) Lateral teeth, Brunei Darussalam (BDMNH, #1). (c) Rachidian tooth, Malaysia (USMMC 00007, #1). (d) Outermost lateral teeth, Malaysia (USMMC 00007, #1). (e) Lateral teeth, detail, Brunei Darussalam (BDMNH, #1). The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a = 40 mm; b = 30 μm; c = 10 μm; d = 20 μm; e = 5 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5182662/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182676>
    dc:description "Figure 13. Radula, Melayonchis siongkiati. (a) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth, Malaysia (USMMC 00016,#2). (b) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth, same as (a). (c) Outermost lateral teeth,same as (a). (d) Lateral teeth, same as (a). (e) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth, Brunei Darussalam, station 30 (BDMNH, #1). (f) Lateral teeth, inferior view, same as (e). The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a, d = 40 μm; b, c, e = 20 μm; f = 4 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5182676/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182686>
    dc:description "Figure 18. Radula, Melayonchis annae, Singapore (ZRC.MOL.6503, #2). (a) Median region of left half rows. (b) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth. (c) Lateral teeth, inferior view. (d) Outermost lateral teeth. (e) Lateral teeth. The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a = 100 μm; b, d, e = 20 μm; c = 4 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5182686/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182698>
    dc:description "Figure 24. Radula, Melayonchis aileenae, Malaysia (USMMC 00019, #2). (a) Median region of left half rows. (b) Rachidian and innermost teeth. (c) Rachidian and innermost teeth. (d) Outermost lateral teeth. (e) Lateral teeth. The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a = 40 μm; b, e = 10 μm; c, d = 5 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5182698/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182700>
    dc:description "Figure 25. Radula, Melayonchis aileenae, Malaysia. (a) Innermost lateral and lateral teeth (USMMC 00019, #1). (b) Rachidian tooth (USMMC 00019, #1). (c) Lateral teeth, inferior view (USMMC 00019, #1). (d) Outermost lateral teeth (USMMC 00021). The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Sclae bars: a, d = 20 μm; b, c = 5 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5182700/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

